PIPELINE 1: CUI REDUCTION
Goal: Raw text → extract medical concepts → filter → deduplicate → surviving CUIs.
Same pipeline for queries and documents. Ensures centroids are comparable.
Query: "knee arthroplasty" — Document: Case 1 (asthma, 25 phrases, 691 raw CUIs)

Stage 1: CUI Extraction + Clinical Context
Send text to UMLS extraction API. Vector similarity search over 2.3M UMLS concepts. Returns closest CUIs.
ParameterValueTypeWhy this valueTOP_K6CONFIGWas 3. Short phrases ("pain", "fever") had correct CUI at rank 4-5. 6 gives safety margin without noise.TOP_P5000CONFIGCandidate pool before ranking. Diminishing returns past 5000.COMBINEDTrueCONFIGPhrase + context sentence concatenated before embedding. Without context, "cold" = temperature or common cold. ~15-20% precision gain.CLUSTER_SET"umls"CONFIGFull UMLS. SAB filter narrows later._API_TIMEOUT200sFIXEDAPI can take 30-60s for large batches. 200s = 3× headroom._RETRY3/1s on 429,5xxFIXEDExponential backoff. 401 triggers token refresh instead._GCLOUD_TIMEOUT30sFIXEDToken fetch. Usually <2s, cold start can take 15s.ConText rules102 built-inFIXEDmedspacy (Chapman 2001, Harkema 2009). Zero custom rules.
ConText — how batch_parse() works:
1. Tokenize full document ONCE with spaCy
2. Find each phrase inside the document by string search (not append)
3. Set all phrases as entity spans simultaneously
4. Run ConText ONCE over all spans
→ O(n_tokens) total, not O(n_tokens × n_phrases)
Old code appended phrase to end of document. Notes ending with "no f/u needed" negated everything.
Result: 4 booleans per phrase — negated, historical, hypothetical, family. Negated → all CUIs discarded.
Caching: API result (CUI distances only) is cached. ConText is NEVER cached — same phrase can be negated in one doc and affirmed in another.
For query:
API returns 25 CUIs (top 10):
  C0745532  dist=0.218  Knee arthroplasty prosthesis placement
  C1536796  dist=0.221  Knee arthroplasty (& replacement)
  C0187960  dist=0.224  Prosthetic arthroplasty of knee joint
  C0375841  dist=0.225  Knee joint replacement
  C5768203  dist=0.229  Prosthetic arthroplasty of right knee
  ... plus 15 more (ICD10PCS codes)

ConText: negated=0, historical=0 → all 25 survive
For document:
25 phrases → each sent to API separately:
  "severe persistent asthma"  → 28 CUIs
  "allergic rhinitis"         → 33 CUIs
  "shortness of breath"       → 41 CUIs (39 are ICD10CM — removed in Stage 2)
  ... 25 phrases total        → 691 raw CUIs (550 unique)

Stage 2: SAB Filter
Keep only CUIs from allowed source vocabularies.
ParameterValueTypeWhy this valueALLOWED_SABS{"SNOMEDCT_US"}CONFIGUMLS has 200+ vocabularies with massive duplication. SNOMED CT US = one clean hierarchy. ICD10 is billing. Add RXNORM for meds, LNC for labs if needed. Don't mix hierarchies — SNOMED says A is parent of B, ICD10 says B is parent of A. Stage 4 breaks.
For query: 25 → 10 (15 ICD10PCS removed)
For document: 691 → ~280. "Shortness of breath" goes from 41 → 2 (39 were ICD10CM).

Stage 3: Metadata + IC
Fetch semantic types from BigQuery. Look up IC from precomputed dict.
ParameterValueTypeWhy this value_BQ_BATCH5,000FIXEDBQ practical limit ~10K. 5K balances query size vs round-trips._BQ_TIMEOUT300sFIXEDCold cache: 30-60s. 300s covers worst-case.IC formula−log((desc+1)/total)FIXEDResnik 1995. +1 = Laplace smoothing. Higher IC = more specific concept.IC_PATHic_precomputed.pklCONFIGPrecomputed for 2.3M nodes (~15 min). Runtime = O(1) dict lookup.
For query: 10 → 10 (all valid SNOMED procedures)
For document: ~280 → ~270 (few deprecated concepts removed)

Stage 4: Hierarchy Reduction
If a parent CUI and its child are both in the surviving set, remove the parent.
ParameterValueTypeWhy this valueancestor_depthComputed (SNOMED→5)ADAPTIVElog(20)/log(mean_in_degree), clamped [1,5]. Targets ~20 ancestors per CUI. For SNOMED (mean_in ~1.8): log(20)/log(1.8) = 5.08 → 5. Computed once from the graph (2.3M nodes), not from the query or document. Same value every run. Only changes if you swap the hierarchy file._ANCESTOR_TARGET20FIXED20 ancestors = mid-level of most UMLS branches. Enough for grouping, not so many you hit root._ANCESTOR_DEPTH_CLAMP(1, 5)FIXEDMin 1 = always check direct parents. Max 5 = never deeper even in sparse hierarchies.DirectionUP, 1 hopFIXEDOnly graph.predecessors(). Multi-hop would compare cousins — too aggressive.RuleIC(child) ≥ IC(parent) + same typeFIXEDKeep the more specific concept. Semantic type check prevents removing a Disease parent when child is a Procedure.
For query:
10 → 8
REMOVED: C0086511 (Knee Replacement Arthroplasty)
  KEPT: C0845658 (Total arthroplasty of knee, unilateral)
  → child IC ≥ parent IC, same type (Procedure)

REMOVED: C0375841 (Knee joint replacement)
  KEPT: C0187960 (Prosthetic arthroplasty of knee joint)
For document: ~270 → ~209

Stage 5: Embedding Reduction (Louvain + Otsu + Guards)
Fetch 3072-dim embeddings. Find and remove near-duplicate CUIs (same concept, different SNOMED code).
Two paths:

n ≤ 20: fast path — Otsu + guards only
n > 20: full path — Louvain → communities → Otsu + guards within each

Size Gate
ParameterValueTypeWhy this value_LOUVAIN_MIN_CUIS20FIXED= k_neighbors. When n ≤ k, k-NN graph is fully connected — Louvain finds noise, not structure.
k-NN Graph (full path only)
ParameterValueTypeWhy this valuek_neighbors20FIXEDChoi 2016, Wang 2018 (biomedical). <10 too sparse. >30 over-merges.Edge thresholdmean(k-th dists)ADAPTIVEFor each CUI, find 20 nearest neighbors from 60×60 similarity matrix. Record distance to 20th neighbor. 60 numbers, one per CUI. Average them. NOT the mean of 1,770 pairwise distances._KNN_BLOCK_SIZE2000FIXEDMemory optimization. 2000 rows at a time prevents OOM.
CUI                     20th neighbor dist   meaning
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Severe asthma                  0.25           dense neighborhood
Albuterol                      0.30           moderate
Chest X-ray                    0.48           sparse
Follow-up visit                0.52           sparse

Edge threshold = mean of 60 values ≈ 0.38
Edge added only if neighbor distance < 0.38
Louvain Community Detection
ParameterValueTypeWhy this valueresolution1.0FIXEDStandard. Higher = more communities. Lower = fewer._RANDOM_SEED42FIXEDReproducible. Same input → same communities every run.
How it works:
Start: 60 communities of 1

Phase 1: for each CUI, try moving to each neighbor's community.
  "Severe asthma" → try "Acute severe asthma" community → modularity +0.12 (best)
  "Severe asthma" → try "Albuterol" community → modularity +0.01 (worse)
  → join "Acute severe asthma"
  Repeat until no move improves.

Phase 2: collapse communities into super-nodes. Repeat Phase 1.
Repeat until stable.

Result: ~6 communities that happen to align with clinical categories:
  community 0: asthma severity CUIs
  community 1: respiratory findings
  community 2: medications
  community 3: lab values
  community 4: procedures
  community 5: encounters

ALL 60 CUIS STILL HERE. Louvain groups, removes nothing.
Otsu Threshold (within each community)
ParameterValueTypeWhy this valueOtsu thresholdData-drivenADAPTIVEMax between-class variance (Otsu 1979). Computed per community from that community's pairwise distances.Otsu guardrailmedian(distances)ADAPTIVECap at median. At most 50% of pairs are candidates.
Take community 0 (10 asthma CUIs). 10×10 matrix → 45 pairwise distances. Sort:
pair                                               dist    what it really is
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Severe asthma attack ↔ Acute severe asthma         0.008   same concept, different code
Mild persistent uncntrl ↔ Mild persistent+rhinitis 0.012   same concept, different code
(pair 3)                                           0.015   same concept, different code
(pair 4)                                           0.018   same concept, different code

                    ─── natural gap ───

Mild persistent ↔ Moderate persistent              0.095   different severity — NOT duplicate
Moderate ↔ Severe persistent                       0.110   different severity
...41 more pairs up to 0.22...
Otsu splits these 45 distance values into "close pairs" and "far pairs". Tries every candidate. Picks the one where the two sides are most different:
candidate = 0.012:
  close pairs: {0.008}                       mean = 0.008
  far pairs:   {0.012, 0.015, ... 0.22}      mean = 0.128
  score = (1/45) × (44/45) × (0.008 − 0.128)² = 0.0003  (only 1 below — weak split)

candidate = 0.095:                                          ← THE GAP
  close pairs: {0.008, 0.012, 0.015, 0.018}  mean = 0.013  (the duplicates)
  far pairs:   {0.095, 0.110, ... 0.22}       mean = 0.145  (different concepts)
  score = (4/45) × (41/45) × (0.013 − 0.145)² = 0.00143  (HIGHEST — clean split)

candidate = 0.110:
  close pairs: {0.008...0.095}               mean = 0.047
  far pairs:   {0.110, ... 0.22}             mean = 0.158
  score = 0.00098  (mixes duplicates with non-duplicates — worse)

Winner: threshold = 0.095. Cap at median (0.12) — 0.095 < 0.12, no cap.
Otsu does NOT remove anything. It draws a line:

Below 0.095: "suspicious — check with guards"
Above 0.095: "definitely different — skip"

Each community gets its own threshold:
community 0 (asthma):      0.095  (severity variants moderately spread)
community 2 (medications): 0.050  (drug names cluster tightly)
community 5 (encounters):  0.120  (encounter types more spread out)
Structural Guards
For each pair below threshold: 4 guards check. ANY says "different" → keep both. ALL fail → remove lower-IC one.
GuardCostFires whenWhyG1: Hierarchy edgeO(1)One is direct parent of otherParent-child = different specificity. Both needed.G2: Semantic typesO(|types|)Drug vs Disease, Device vs ProcedureEmbeddings put drugs near diseases they treat. Ontologically different.G3: Ancestor setsO(n) BFS [1,5]Zero shared ancestorsCompletely different UMLS branches.G4: Sibling leavesO(1)Both leaf nodes, same parentLeft knee vs right knee. Merging destroys laterality.
Worked examples:
C0264429 (Severe asthma attack) vs C0264423 (Acute severe asthma)
  dist=0.008, below 0.095
  G1: parent-child?   NO
  G2: types disjoint? NO (both Disease)
  G3: ancestors?      NO (share Persistent asthma)
  G4: sibling leaves? NO
  → ALL FAILED → REMOVE C0264429 (lower IC)

C0004096 (Asthma) vs C0264408 (Severe persistent asthma)
  dist=0.03, below 0.095
  G1: parent-child?   YES — Asthma is parent
  → STOP. KEEP BOTH.

C3873937 (Knee femur prosthesis) [Device] vs C0188146 (Arthroplasty) [Procedure]
  dist=0.12, below threshold
  G1: NO
  G2: YES — Device ≠ Procedure
  → STOP. KEEP BOTH.
Singleton Merging
ParameterValueTypeWhy this valuemerge_min_simmean(within-group) × 0.5ADAPTIVESingleton must be 50% as similar to group as group members are to each other. Clamped [0.1, 0.9]._COSINE_FALLBACK_THRESHOLD0.5FIXEDFallback when no multi-member groups exist. Rare.
