PIPELINE 3: QUERY MATCHING (ADAPTIVE SCORER)
Goal: Compare query topics against stored document topic groups → score → rank → return.
Query: "knee arthroplasty" (1 topic, 5 CUIs, 1 centroid)
Store: 5 documents, 236 topic groups total

Fixed Parameters
ParameterValueTypeWhy this valuez_score_normalizeTrueCONFIGAuto-weights 3 signals by discriminative power for THIS query. Broad query → vec_sim has high variance → dominates. Specific → cui_ratio dominates. Can't do this with fixed weights.w_cui / w_vec / w_lin0.40 / 0.30 / 0.30CONFIGManual mode only (z_score=False). 0.40 for CUI overlap = strongest evidence. 0.30/0.30 equal because neither vec nor lin is systematically stronger.anc_depth8CONFIGDeeper at search time (vs 3-5 at ingestion) to find ALL hierarchy relationships. 8 hops reaches mid-UMLS (IC ~3-4). Deeper adds no matches because IC pruning stops it.score_ratio0.40CONFIGReturn results ≥ 40% of best score. 0.30 = noise. 0.60 = misses secondaries. Adapts to data: could return 1 or 50.score_min0.01CONFIGStructural floor. Catches float artifacts from z-score. Not a tuning knob.Zero-evidence guardall 3 == 0.0FIXEDSuppress only if ALL signals are literally 0.0. No per-signal thresholds — those killed broad queries where only one signal carries evidence.group_dist0.15CONFIGCross-chunk grouping. 0.15 = 85% cosine sim. Tested: 0.10 under-groups, 0.25 over-groups.variant_min_change1CONFIGMin CUI adds+removes to flag a variant. 1 = any change flagged.

Adaptive Parameters (computed at runtime from store data)
ParameterFormulaValue for this storeWhyfilter_min_ancestor_icp25(store CUI ICs)13.98Ancestors below this are too broad to be meaningful shared ancestors. Specific store → high floor. General store → low floor.ic_weight_alphaquery_ic_mean / max_store_ic, clamped [0.1, 0.9]0.90Specific query against specific store → IC dominates over IDF. Broad query → IDF dominates.ic_prune_ratiop10/p50(store ICs), clamped [0.1, 0.9]0.711Controls BFS pruning depth. Specific store (narrow IC range) → tight. General → relaxed.sibling_ic_ratiop25/p75(store ICs), clamped [0.1, 0.95]0.944MICA IC gate for sibling matching. Specific store → only very close siblings.use_idfShannon entropy of IDF > 0.3TrueHigh entropy = IDF values spread out = discriminative. Low = adds noise.min_best_lin2×root_ic / (q_ic+store_ic) × 1.5, clamped [0.03, 0.35]0.278Lin of two unrelated CUIs sharing only root. Below = no more related than random. ChunkMatcher hard-negative blocker only.

Pass 1: Topic Gate
Performance optimization, not a hard gate. If nothing passes → score ALL groups.
Step 1 — Centroid gate: query centroid × 236 group centroids (matrix multiply). gap_split finds threshold.
Step 2 — CUI overlap rescue: excluded groups checked for shared CUIs with query.
Step 3 — Fallback: if nothing passed both → score ALL groups in Pass 2.
Before Pass 2: ancestors precomputed for all doc CUIs in admitted groups. Without this, hierarchy matching silently returns 0 (the bug we fixed). Also: topic_cui included in matchable set (another bug — grouping ancestor was invisible to scorer).
For "knee arthroplasty":
  Step 1: 1 group clears centroid gate (case_2)
  Step 2: group 71 shares C3873937 (Knee femur prosthesis) → admitted
  → 2/236 groups to Pass 2

Pass 2: CUI Scoring (Three Signals)
Each entry in admitted groups scored individually.
Signal 1 — cui_ratio (IC-weighted CUI overlap):

Exact CUI intersection
Parent-child (8-hop BFS, IC-pruned from hop 3)
Sibling matching via MICA (Most Informative Common Ancestor)
Penalty: d_ic/q_ic for subsumption
IDF and IC blended via adaptive alpha

Signal 2 — vec_sim (cosine similarity):

dot(query centroid, topic centroid)
Captures relationships hierarchy can't see: "worsening" (qualifier) co-occurs with "heart failure" (disease)

Signal 3 — lin_avg (Lin similarity):

For each non-exact query CUI, find best Lin against all topic members
Lin(A,B) = 2 × IC(MICA) / (IC(A) + IC(B))
Measures structural agreement in hierarchy

case_2:
  cui_ratio = 0.38
    exact:     C5768203 (Prosthetic arthroplasty of R knee) ✓
    hierarchy: C0188146 via parent-child ✓
    hierarchy: C5688901 via MICA ✓
    → 3/5 matched, with subsumption penalties

  vec_sim = high (both knee arthroplasty embeddings)

  lin_avg = 0.617 (strong hierarchy agreement for unmatched CUIs)
Why three signals?

"fever and chills" → matches via cui_ratio (exact CUI overlap)
"worsening condition" → matches via vec_sim only (qualifiers and diseases are in different branches — no CUI overlap, no hierarchy match, but embeddings capture co-occurrence)
"OA of left knee" → "Osteoarthritis" → matches via lin_avg (parent-child hierarchy)
No single signal covers all cases.


Pass 3: Z-Score Normalization
Each signal z-normalized across all candidates:
z = (value − mean) / std
Final score = z_cui + z_vec + z_lin, shifted to [0,1].
The highest-variance signal gets the most weight automatically. If cui_ratio varies a lot (some candidates match, some don't) but vec_sim is flat (all similar embeddings), cui_ratio dominates.
If ALL candidates identical (z-scores flat) → falls back to w_cui/w_vec/w_lin (0.40/0.30/0.30).
case_2 normalized: 1.000 (highest)

Pass 4: Relative Threshold + Results
Trust the combined score. Return all results that are relevant.
best_score = 1.000
threshold  = 1.000 × 0.40 = 0.400
score_min  = 0.01 (structural floor)

Zero-evidence: no candidates have all 3 at 0.0
Dedup: one result per chunk_id

Result:
  #1  case_2  score=1.000  cui=0.38  lin=0.617
      matched: C0188146, C5688901, C5768203

1 result. Other 4 docs are asthma/diabetes — below 0.400. Correct.
Why score_ratio not gap_split?
gap_split finds the single biggest gap. Scores: 0.82, 0.49, 0.45, 0.41, 0.12. Gap between 0.82 and 0.49 → returns only 1. But 0.49/0.45/0.41 are all clinically relevant. score_ratio=0.40 keeps all four (≥0.328) and drops only the noise (0.12).
How many results?
No fixed cap. Could be 1 or 50 depending on data. top_k in caller is optional UI pagination, not a relevance cutoff.

LLM Reasoning (optional)
Top results sent to Gemini with matched CUIs, topic labels, chunk text.
Verdict for case_2: "Good" — total knee arthroplasty of right knee. Two query concepts not covered: tibial plateau, robotic assistance.

